### Setup TourOperator for testing

### 1. Register a new TourOperator user
POST https://localhost:7012/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "touroperator@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "userName": "TestTourOperator",
  "roleName": "Tour Operator"
}

### 2. Login as TourOperator
POST https://localhost:7012/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "touroperator@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Create TourOperator record (if needed)
POST https://localhost:7012/api/TourOperator
Authorization: Bearer {{tour_operator_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1,
  "companyName": "Test Tour Company",
  "phoneNumber": "1234567890",
  "address": "123 Test Street",
  "description": "Test tour operator company"
}

### 4. Test GetNotesByTourOperator
GET https://localhost:7012/api/GuideNote/tour-operator/notes
Authorization: Bearer {{tour_operator_token}}

### 5. Test UpdateNoteExtraCost (if notes exist)
PUT https://localhost:7012/api/GuideNote/notes/1/extra-cost
Authorization: Bearer {{tour_operator_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "extraCost": 50.00
} 